                                <condition>Much of the margins has been torn away, encroaching in
                                    the lower outer corner into the written area, with some loss of
                                    text. Strips of Japanese paper have been used to stabilise this
                                    area of damage. In the upper outer corner a parchment patch has
                                    been attached in an earlier repair. There are numerous
                                    worm-holes and other small holes in the leaf. There is purple
                                    mould staining, significant water staining and areas of dirt,
                                    and discoloration due to the presence of glue when this fragment
                                    was used in the binding of another book. The ink is faded in
                                    places.</condition>
                            </supportDesc>
                            
