                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote scope="sole" xml:id="hand-1">
                                <p>The text was copied in a <term type="script">mixed minuscule
                                    bouletée</term> script, slanting slightly to the left, in
                                    brown ink, with minimal variation in letter size.</p>
                                <p>Syllabic abbreviations are not used, except the horizontal stroke
                                    for <hi rend="italic">nu</hi>, which appears only at the end of
                                    lines, while superscript word endings do not appear. Acute and
                                    grave accents are often almost horizontal, while breathings are
                                    angular and usually very extremely small. Mute <hi rend="italic">iota</hi> is absent. There is decorative use of the double
                                    dot, and where it appears on the first letter of a word, the
                                    breathing is omitted.</p>
                                <p>Punctuation used includes the middle and upper points and the
                                    lower and middle commas.</p>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                        
                        <decoDesc>
                            <decoNote type="plainInit">The beginnings of sections are marked by
                                minor initials in brown ink.</decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>
                        
                        <additions>There are some pen-trials in the margins. The fragment has been
                            marked with the present classmark and the former classmark
                            T.13.</additions>
